This article is a presidential proclamation issued by President Barack Obama on December 14, 2012, in response to the shooting tragedy in Newtown, Connecticut. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on December 18, 2012. It also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff for the same length of time at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.